  <Callout type="tip" title="Customizing shortcuts">
    All keyboard shortcuts can be customized in <strong>Settings &rarr; Keyboard Shortcuts</strong>.
    You can also view the current shortcut for any action by hovering over its menu item or
    toolbar button.
  </Callout>

  <h2 id="customization">Customization</h2>

  <p>
    Arris supports full keyboard shortcut customization. Open <strong>Settings &rarr;
    Keyboard Shortcuts</strong> to see all available actions and their current bindings.
  </p>

  <ul>
    <li><strong>Rebind</strong> &mdash; click any shortcut to enter a new key combination.</li>
    <li><strong>Reset</strong> &mdash; right-click a customized shortcut to restore the default.</li>
    <li><strong>Conflicts</strong> &mdash; if two actions share the same shortcut, a warning badge appears. The action with higher context specificity wins.</li>
    <li><strong>Export</strong> &mdash; shortcut configurations are stored in <code>settings.json</code> and can be shared across machines by copying the file.</li>
  </ul>

  <p>
    Shortcuts follow macOS conventions. The modifier key symbols used throughout the app and this documentation are:
  </p>

  <ul>
    <li><kbd>&#8984;</kbd> &mdash; Command</li>
    <li><kbd>&#8679;</kbd> &mdash; Shift</li>
    <li><kbd>&#8997;</kbd> &mdash; Option / Alt</li>
    <li><kbd>&#8963;</kbd> &mdash; Control</li>
    <li><kbd>&#8617;</kbd> &mdash; Return / Enter</li>
    <li><kbd>&#9003;</kbd> &mdash; Delete / Backspace</li>
  </ul>
